    "How does a home appraisal work?",
    "A home appraisal is an independent professional estimate of market value ordered by your lender and paid by you (typically $400–$600). The process: (1) Lender orders from an AMC (Appraisal Management Company) — you can't choose your appraiser. (2) Appraiser schedules a site visit (1–2 hours). They measure the home, note condition, features, and improvements. (3) Research: appraiser identifies 3–6 comparable sales (comps) within the past 6 months, ideally within 1 mile. (4) Analysis: adjustments are made for differences (extra bathroom +$10,000, updated kitchen +$15,000, etc.). (5) Report: appraiser issues a formal report using Fannie Mae Form 1004. Typically takes 7–21 days from ordering. (6) Lender reviews and either accepts or orders a re-review. If the appraisal equals or exceeds purchase price, great — proceed. If it comes in below, you face the appraisal gap."
